Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.47,0:20:09.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不会的 -会的\N{\fs90}- No, it wouldn't. - It would!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.04,0:20:11.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,没必要再争了\N{\fs90}There's no point arguing anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.61,0:20:13.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,他过完阿尔法罗密欧的瘾了\N{\fs90}He's got the Alfa Romeo thing out of his system,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.52,0:20:15.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是好事 因为接下来到了\N{\fs90}which is good, because it's time now
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.44,0:20:17.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,让我们享受在阳光灿烂的唠嗑街人行道上\N{\fs90}for us to enjoy a gentle stroll
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.10,0:20:20.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,悠闲漫步\N{\fs90}along the sunlit sidewalks of Conversation Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.29,0:20:31.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这片头不错-我挺喜欢的\N{\fs90}- That's a good one. - I like that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.46,0:20:32.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,确实不错 好了好了\N{\fs90}It is. Right, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.20,0:20:37.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 我们先从这个说起\N{\fs90}OK. And we start with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.61,0:20:39.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,阿尔法罗密欧的Stelvio\N{\fs90}It's the new Alfa Romeo Stelvio.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.01,0:20:43.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你饶了我吧-这可是非常重要的新闻\N{\fs90}-  For God's sake! - This is important news.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.21,0:20:46.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,压根就不是重要新闻 这是给白痴看的朋友圈新闻\N{\fs90}It's not important news. It's niche news for morons.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.24,0:20:49.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,拉倒吧 这车很棒的\N{\fs90}It's not! It's a superb car,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.07,0:20:49.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你能得到\N{\fs90}because you can have it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.87,0:20:51.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,和Quadriplegio一样的\N{\fs90}with the same 500 horsepower engine
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.55,0:20:53.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,500马力引擎\N{\fs90}that you get in the Quadriplegio.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.41,0:20:56.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,除了这个 还有四轮驱动\N{\fs90}And with that... with that you get four-wheel-drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.78,0:20:58.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,那就是说这车能在雨天开 是不是\N{\fs90}So that one will work in the wet, will it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.72,0:21:01.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 当某人有了孩子\N{\fs90}Hammond, when somebody has a baby,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.50,0:21:03.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,你会上前看一眼然后说\N{\fs90}OK, do you go up to it and...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.38,0:21:04.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 看我新出生的孩子哟\N{\fs90}"Oh, look at my new baby that I've...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.61,0:21:05.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,恶 长得真丑\N{\fs90}Eurgh! It's really ugly!"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.86,0:21:07.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 只有在确实丑的情况\N{\fs90}Well, only if it's ugly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.86,0:21:11.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看看 不能对阿尔法罗密欧太残忍\N{\fs90}You see, you can't be cruel about Alfa Romeos.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.23,0:21:12.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我当然能 -他们也很努力嘛\N{\fs90}- Yes, I can. - They're trying so hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.98,0:21:15.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 那我们继续 忘了阿尔法吧\N{\fs90}Well, let's just move it on. Forget the Alfa, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.47,0:21:18.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在我们来聊聊我们所处的位置\N{\fs90}Now, we should talk about where we are,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.27,0:21:22.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,田纳西州 因为这是本州销量最好的车型了\N{\fs90}OK, Tennessee, because this is the bestselling vehicle in the state.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.11,0:21:24.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fs90}- OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.48,0:21:27.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗯 我还有一张警车的照片\N{\fs90}Yeah, we've got a picture of the police car.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.25,0:21:29.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有救护车\N{\fs90}And an ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.98,0:21:31.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,-然后是灵车\N{\fs90}- And a hearse. -  Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.72,0:21:34.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在推测 推测这里的主题\N{\fs90}I'm detecting... detecting a theme here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.79,0:21:36.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,皮卡 我觉得我说的对\N{\fs90}The pickup truck, I think I'm right,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.56,0:21:38.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这里确实挺受欢迎的 对吧\N{\fs90}is very popular in this neck of the woods, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.83,0:21:40.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,皮卡在英国完全不流行\N{\fs90}I'm sure you may be amazed to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.79,0:21:43.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,你门听到会很惊讶吧\N{\fs90}they really haven't caught on at all in the UK.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.70,0:21:45.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,我是说 几乎没人买\N{\fs90}I mean, almost nobody has one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.52,0:21:47.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,基本上看不到 挺遗憾的\N{\fs90}You hardly see them, which is a shame,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.18,0:21:48.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我很喜欢皮卡\N{\fs90}because I love a pickup truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.30,0:21:50.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,-嗯 我们知道 -我喜欢\N{\fs90} Yeah, we know. - I like a truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.27,0:21:51.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,你知道吗\N{\fs90}- You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.57,0:21:54.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,我可以在这里说\N{\fs90}I can say that here. I can say that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.52,0:21:57.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,这很好 你能说出来 但是这并不是很明智\N{\fs90}That's fine, you can say that, but they're not actually very sensible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.41,0:21:59.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,听着朋友 这又不是全部\N{\fs90}Look, mate, that's not everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.38,0:22:01.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,你开着法拉利出门\N{\fs90}Anyway, you drive around in your Ferrari, OK,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.21,0:22:03.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且乐于忍受强加的赋税\N{\fs90}and happily put up with the compromises that that imposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.44,0:22:05.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,于是你得忍受大量开销 不便\N{\fs90}So you put up with the cost, the inconvenience,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.55,0:22:07.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且这也不舒服因为它是辆快车\N{\fs90}and it's not very comfortable because it's a fast car.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.69,0:22:10.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,在皮卡上一样的道理 你要忍受的是\N{\fs90}Same with a pickup. You put up with compromises:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.02,0:22:12.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,重量 尺寸 还有油耗\N{\fs90}the weight, the size, the fuel consumption...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.52,0:22:13.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,那么优点呢\N{\fs90}But what's the upside?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.58,0:22:15.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,这可是辆皮卡啊 你能用它\N{\fs90}It's a pickup truck! You can use it...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.47,0:22:16.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,你能用它装木头\N{\fs90}You can put logs in it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.81,0:22:19.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者 从森林把树拖出来\N{\fs90}and tow... tow trees out of the woods with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.78,0:22:21.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,往里面放头熊\N{\fs90}You could put a bear in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.21,0:22:23.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 你在传媒公司工作啊\N{\fs90}Hammond, you work... you work in the media!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.87,0:22:25.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,唯一需要放在车后的也就只有\N{\fs90}The only thing you have to put in the back of a vehicle
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.71,0:22:28.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,各种联欢餐会的请柬了吧\N{\fs90}are invitations to gala lunches.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.21,0:22:30.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好吧 -仅限于此了吧\N{\fs90}- Well... - That's all you ever do.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.21,0:22:31.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,问题是 实际上在英国\N{\fs90}The problem, actually, in Britain
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.50,0:22:33.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,开一辆皮卡车 不得不承认的\N{\fs90}with a pickup truck-- I'm sorry to admit this--
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.38,0:22:36.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是当你在等红灯的时候\N{\fs90}is that if you pulled up at a set of traffic lights
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.30,0:22:37.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,车后放着你的水泥搅拌器\N{\fs90}and you had your cement mixer
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.72,0:22:38.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,和电锯\N{\fs90}and your chainsaw in the back,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.75,0:22:41.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,马上 这些东西就会被偷走\N{\fs90}they would be stolen immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.64,0:22:43.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,在英国任何放在公共场合的的东西\N{\fs90}Anything left in the open in Britain,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.55,0:22:45.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,就好比聚会上的零食一样 大家随便拿\N{\fs90}it's like nuts at a party, you just help yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.07,0:22:48.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,-为什么这里不会发生呢\N{\fs90}- So why doesn't that happen here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.61,0:22:49.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,现场谁有皮卡？\N{\fs90}Who's got a pickup truck here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.83,0:22:52.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我的天 不可思议\N{\fs90}- Holy cow! That's unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.20,0:22:54.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,当你们出去购物 把东西放在货斗里\N{\fs90}When you go shopping and put things in the back,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.92,0:22:56.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,怎么没有人顺手牵羊呢\N{\fs90}why doesn't someone just help themselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.70,0:22:58.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这里他们可以开枪\N{\fs90}Because they shoot them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.61,0:23:02.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 就是这样\N{\fs90} Well, there is that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.34,0:23:06.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,确实如此 谢了 特朗普\N{\fs90}There is that. Thank you, Donald!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.78,0:23:09.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过为啥 你们有没有在\N{\fs90}But why... Have you ever had anything stolen
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.41,0:23:10.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,等红灯的时候被偷过\N{\fs90}when you were at a red light?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.52,0:23:12.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,从来没有 有没有人被偷过\N{\fs90}Never? Has anyone ever had anything...?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.22,0:23:13.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没有 -真的没有\N{\fs90}- AUDIENCE: No. - No?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.92,0:23:15.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,我以为这里会是\N{\fs90}I thought this was supposed to be
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.39,0:23:17.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,在美国犯罪猖狂的地方\N{\fs90}crime-ridden in America.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.26,0:23:18.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,也许人家都很老实\N{\fs90}Maybe people are honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.92,0:23:19.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不知道 很有可能\N{\fs90}I don't know, it's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.89,0:23:20.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,要是我在英国\N{\fs90}If I was in Britain
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.93,0:23:22.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,看见皮卡后面放了个割草机\N{\fs90}and saw a pickup truck with a lawnmower,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.67,0:23:23.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,"这是我的了"\N{\fs90}"I'll have that."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.87,0:23:28.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,言归正传 昨天我们去了趟\N{\fs90}Now, yesterday we went to erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.37,0:23:30.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,像是个大的经典车博物馆\N{\fs90}It was like a big classic-car museum,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.87,0:23:33.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,就在镇子外面 那里还能把展车买下来\N{\fs90}just out of town here, where you could also buy the exhibits.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.55,0:23:35.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,-很有意思 -很棒的一次经历\N{\fs90}- It's great fun. - It was a fantastic day out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.87,0:23:37.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在那里很开心\N{\fs90}Really enjoyed ourselves in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.21,0:23:38.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,我是说 那都是些 你懂的\N{\fs90}I mean, it was full of, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.41,0:23:40.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,野马和科迈罗之类的\N{\fs90}Mustangs and Camaros and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.15,0:23:41.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,像这样的东西 我这里有张照片\N{\fs90}Stuff like this. We've got a picture
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.58,0:23:43.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,60到70年代的东西\N{\fs90}of this sort of thing-- '60s and '70s stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.22,0:23:47.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们都知道长这样的车 开起来很糟糕\N{\fs90}Now, we know that cars like this are horrible to drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.44,0:23:47.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,吓人\N{\fs90}Terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.95,0:23:49.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过它们看起来特别酷炫\N{\fs90}But they're tremendous to look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.98,0:23:53.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,那时的车辆设计的都很有意思\N{\fs90}There was so much joy in car design back then,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.75,0:23:55.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,你看看那辆车\N{\fs90}and you see it in that car there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.06,0:23:57.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,这其实有点令人伤感\N{\fs90}It actually made us slightly sad in a way, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.46,0:24:00.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我们离开以后 我们突然开始思考\N{\fs90}because as we were leaving, we suddenly started wondering,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.30,0:24:01.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个博物馆里会放什么 \N{\fs90}"Well, what are they gonna put in that museum
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.84,0:24:03.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,在接下来的40年里\N{\fs90}in 40 years' time?"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.61,0:24:04.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,-嗯-什么\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.27,0:24:10.98,注释,,0,0,0,,日产JUKE,道奇DART,样式奇特 常遭吐槽
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.27,0:24:05.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,日产特么的JUKE\N{\fs90}The Nissan-bloody-Juke.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.81,0:24:06.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没错\N{\fs90}- Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.74,0:24:08.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,我可不想现在看到它\N{\fs90}I don't want to look at that now.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.48,0:24:10.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没错 或者来个道奇dart\N{\fs90}- No, exactly. Or the Dodge Dart.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.98,0:24:14.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,小孩以后会说 爸爸\N{\fs90}Well, what child's gonna say, "Oh, Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.44,0:24:17.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,咱们去博物馆看40年车龄的Dart好吗\N{\fs90}Daddy, let's go and look at the 40-year-old Dart in the museum"?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.58,0:24:18.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,没人会去的\N{\fs90}Nobody is!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.69,0:24:20.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,确实现在的汽车设计\N{\fs90}It's true that car design
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.12,0:24:21.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,变得越来越枯燥了\N{\fs90}has become so dreary lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.64,0:24:22.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且我认为部分原因是\N{\fs90}And I think part of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.69,0:24:24.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,大部分汽车设计者们\N{\fs90}it's almost as if the people who design cars
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.87,0:24:26.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,并没有那么喜欢车\N{\fs90}don't actually like cars that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.75,0:24:28.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,正是 但那时候的人确实爱车 你能看出来\N{\fs90}Exactly. But they did then. You can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.70,0:24:30.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,当时Cuba旁边停着辆普利茅斯Fury\N{\fs90}There was a Cuda in there next to a Plymouth Fury,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.90,0:24:34.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,我站在那里看了一个小时 沉浸其中不可自拔\N{\fs90}and I just stood for about an hour, just soaking them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.00,0:24:37.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,我看到辆1966年凯迪拉克\N{\fs90}I saw a 1966 Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.18,0:24:38.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里有张图 看看\N{\fs90}We've got a picture of it here. Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.64,0:24:40.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆车我所喜欢的是\N{\fs90}Now, what I like about this
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.10,0:24:42.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,设计机盖的这哥们\N{\fs90}is that the bloke who designed the bonnet,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.30,0:24:43.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,他想 我设计好了机盖\N{\fs90}he thought, "I've finished with the bonnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.98,0:24:44.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,再设计前脸\N{\fs90}I'll do the grill."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.81,0:24:46.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是他并没有告诉设计尾翼的那帮人\N{\fs90}But he didn't tell the blokes doing the wings,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.45,0:24:49.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后他们就接着搞 结果车长向后延伸了一尺多\N{\fs90}and they kept going, so it goes like another foot.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.61,0:24:52.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过这车看着很棒\N{\fs90}No, but this is fantastic with a fantastic-looking car.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.21,0:24:54.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,别克Riviera 博物馆里有一辆\N{\fs90}The Buick Riviera, they had one of those in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.12,0:24:56.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,-看看这车 -真是赞\N{\fs90}- Look at that! - That is glorious!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.21,0:24:56.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,我有一辆这样的\N{\fs90}I had one of those
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.82,0:24:58.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,是我小时候的玩具车\N{\fs90}as a toy when I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.53,0:25:00.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你把手指头从后窗伸过去\N{\fs90}If you put your finger over the back window,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.44,0:25:01.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,它还会闪灯\N{\fs90}it flashed its lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.93,0:25:03.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后你就这样看着 不禁会想\N{\fs90}And you just look and you go,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.46,0:25:05.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,别克是怎么在30到40年里从设计那样的车型\N{\fs90}"How can Buick have gone from doing that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.77,0:25:08.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,沦落到现在这种\N{\fs90}"in, what, 30-40 years, to doing this,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.44,0:25:09.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,不管这可是棕色 看看吧\N{\fs90}whatever this brown..." Look at...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.78,0:25:11.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他们怎么做到的\N{\fs90}- How have they done that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.95,0:25:13.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,雪佛兰也是\N{\fs90}And it's the same as Chevrolet.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.61,0:25:15.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,那里有辆1960年的Impala\N{\fs90}There was an Impala in there, 1960.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.58,0:25:18.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看这个 这叫兴奋而不是感动\N{\fs90} Look at that! That is exciting not moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.35,0:25:20.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是60年代的雪佛兰Impala\N{\fs90} That's a Chevy Impala from the '60s.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.61,0:25:21.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们看看现在的样子\N{\fs90}Let's have a look at one from today.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.85,0:25:23.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,-可饶了我吧\N{\fs90}-  Oh, for God's sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.48,0:25:25.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们怎么好意思管那玩意叫Impala\N{\fs90}How do they even have the nerve to call that an Impala?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.01,0:25:26.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,这根本就不是啊\N{\fs90}Because it isn't one.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.01,0:25:28.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,我当时看到一辆科尔维特\N{\fs90}I was looking at a Corvette,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.92,0:25:30.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,70年代的科尔维特\N{\fs90}a '70s Corvette.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.10,0:25:31.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,C3款的\N{\fs90}That's the C3 model,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.35,0:25:32.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你是个科尔维特脑残粉的话\N{\fs90}if you're a Corvette nerd.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.64,0:25:33.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一辆所有宇航员\N{\fs90}This was a car that was driven
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.59,0:25:35.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,都开的车\N{\fs90}by all of the astronauts.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.47,0:25:37.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,-确实-还有炮王迪哥\N{\fs90}-  Exactly. - And Dirk Diggler.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.50,0:25:38.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,-嗯\N{\fs90}-  Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.77,0:25:40.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以说 这车是给\N{\fs90}Ah, so it's a car
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.50,0:25:42.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,毛片演员和宇航员开的咯\N{\fs90}for porn stars and astronauts.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.67,0:25:45.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这标语厉害了   -当今还有什么车\N{\fs90}- What a strapline! - What car is there today
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.27,0:25:47.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,是给宇航员和毛片演员开的\N{\fs90}that could be driven by porn stars and astronauts?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.64,0:25:50.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没有了 -阿尔法\N{\fs90}- There isn't one. MAN: An Alfa!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.55,0:25:53.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,其实 他说得对\N{\fs90}Actually, he's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.75,0:25:56.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,不对不对 宇航员要能够顺利抵达\N{\fs90}No, astronauts have to get there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.58,0:25:58.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,他说得对 说的正是\N{\fs90}He's right! That's exactly
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.41,0:26:00.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,Quadriplegio -别啊\N{\fs90}- what the Quadriplegio is! - No!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.92,0:26:03.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,专为宇航员和毛片演员量身定制的 也就是我\N{\fs90}For porn stars and astronauts, which is what I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.59,0:26:05.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在 我想来聊聊\N{\fs90}Now, I would like to have
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.52,0:26:08.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,纽博格林\N{\fs90}a conversation about the Nürburgring.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.55,0:26:10.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,-说吧-因为这很重要\N{\fs90}- Go on. - Because this is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.24,0:26:11.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,去年 我很高兴的是\N{\fs90}Last year, I was delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.52,0:26:13.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,在德国管理纽博格林的人\N{\fs90}The people who run the Nürburgring in Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.61,0:26:16.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,说他们要禁止厂家在那里\N{\fs90}they said they were gonna ban car manufacturers
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.41,0:26:18.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,给车测圈速了\N{\fs90}from setting lap records there.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.64,0:26:20.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,不好意思 你为啥感到高兴\N{\fs90}Sorry, why were you delighted about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.74,0:26:22.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这想法很棒\N{\fs90}Because that's an excellent idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.55,0:26:24.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你制造的车好到\N{\fs90}If you make a car that is excellent
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.95,0:26:26.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,能在纽博格林测圈速\N{\fs90}for doing a fast lap of the Nürburgring,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.61,0:26:29.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,那么日常生活中这车会很没用\N{\fs90}it would be useless as a car everywhere else in your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.27,0:26:31.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,就好比把你的房子装修成\N{\fs90}It's like... It's like setting your house up
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.28,0:26:32.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,专门用来玩室内真人CS\N{\fs90}to play Laser Quest.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.55,0:26:34.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,玩游戏还不错 \N{\fs90}It will be brilliant for playing Laser Quest,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.89,0:26:36.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过搞个聚餐就很垃圾\N{\fs90}but it'll be rubbish for a dinner party
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.81,0:26:37.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为屋子里全是激光\N{\fs90}because it's full of lasers,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.79,0:26:39.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,漆黑一片 迷雾重重  而且音乐也是\N{\fs90}darkness, fog and music that goes...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.33,0:26:41.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且人们跑来跑去\N{\fs90}...and people running around
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.56,0:26:42.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,想象自己在星球大战当中\N{\fs90}thinking that they're in Star Wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.73,0:26:44.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,换个比方 你养条狗\N{\fs90}Or you could get a dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.06,0:26:46.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,你可以把狗训练成军犬来看门\N{\fs90}You could train a dog as an attack dog,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.38,0:26:48.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你有个废品场\N{\fs90}which is fantastic if you own a scrapyard
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.57,0:26:50.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,这会是不错的选择\N{\fs90}and you need the dog to guard it,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.44,0:26:53.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过要是在家当宠物 它会吃了你的孩子\N{\fs90}but take it home as a pet, it will eat your children.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.55,0:26:54.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,完全没用\N{\fs90}- It's completely useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.95,0:26:55.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是把车拿到\N{\fs90}That's what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.94,0:26:57.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,纽博格林的后果\N{\fs90}when you set a car up for the Nürburgring.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.04,0:26:59.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,这可不是讨论啊 詹姆斯\N{\fs90}This isn't really a conversation, James.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.04,0:27:02.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得这周不小心拐到了怨妇街\N{\fs90}No, I think we've accidentally turned down Rant Lane this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.78,0:27:03.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,-嗯 还没说完呢\N{\fs90}- Well, there's more.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.81,0:27:04.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他又开始了 -不\N{\fs90}He's off again. - No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.75,0:27:07.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,关键在于 真正的坏消息是\N{\fs90}But the thing is, the bad news in all this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.81,0:27:08.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们已经决定\N{\fs90}is that they've decided
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.81,0:27:10.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,将允许汽车制造商\N{\fs90}that they will allow car manufacturers
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.81,0:27:12.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,再次去冲击圈速纪录\N{\fs90}to set lap records again.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.47,0:27:13.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,其实这也挺好\N{\fs90}Well, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.06,0:27:14.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,- 不 这很操蛋 - 好吧\N{\fs90}- No, it's bad! - OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.70,0:27:16.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看那些最近推出的车\N{\fs90}Think of the cars that have come out recently
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.55,0:27:18.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,被不断调试研发\N{\fs90}we've been developed
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.04,0:27:20.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,就为了能在纽北圈速更快\N{\fs90}so that they would go fast around the Nürburgring.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.12,0:27:21.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,BMW的M4 GTS\N{\fs90}BMW M4 GTS,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.81,0:27:23.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,不可否认 它是一台很糟糕的车\N{\fs90}you can't deny it, it's a terrible car.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.64,0:27:25.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,日产GT-R 赛道版\N{\fs90}Nissan GT-R, the Track Edition,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.98,0:27:27.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,也是一台糟糕的车\N{\fs90}that is a terrible car.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.55,0:27:30.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,就连西雅特的Leon Cupra 280,\N{\fs90}Even SEAT-- the SEAT Leon Cupra 280,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.01,0:27:33.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,曾是纽北最快的掀背车\N{\fs90}that's got a hatchback record for going around the Nürburgring,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.55,0:27:34.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,简直就是垃圾\N{\fs90}and it's rubbish!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.51,0:27:36.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,纽博格林就是在毁车\N{\fs90}The Nürburgring ruins cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.04,0:27:38.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,我在开发一个手机应用\N{\fs90}I'm developing an app for the smart phone
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.70,0:27:39.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,叫做“炸掉纽博格林”\N{\fs90}called Bomb The Nürburgring
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.92,0:27:41.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,遥控一架道尼17号轰炸机到纽北\N{\fs90}where you guide a Dornier 17 over it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.01,0:27:43.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后炸个满天飞\N{\fs90}and blow it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.38,0:27:45.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,你来这节目干嘛的\N{\fs90}What are you doing on this programme?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.44,0:27:46.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,来讲道理的\N{\fs90}- Talking sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.84,0:27:48.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,问得好 我也不知道\N{\fs90}Good question. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.29,0:27:51.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,英国有个主持烘焙节目的老奶奶\N{\fs90}We have this old woman who has a baking show in Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.58,0:27:52.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,叫做玛丽·贝莉\N{\fs90}She's called Mary Berry.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.67,0:27:54.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们可能知道她\N{\fs90}It would be... You probably know her.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.47,0:27:55.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像听她说\N{\fs90}It's probably the same
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.84,0:27:58.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,“我讨厌蛋糕”一样\N{\fs90}as her saying, "I hate cakes!"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.15,0:27:59.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\fs90} Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.01,0:28:00.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,玛丽·贝莉也会同意我的观点\N{\fs90}Mary Berry would agree with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.51,0:28:02.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果她做了一个蛋糕\N{\fs90}because if she made a cake
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.24,0:28:03.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后在纽北赛道调试\N{\fs90}that had been developed on the Nürburgring,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.01,0:28:06.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,就会有人在蛋糕顶上放一个洋葱圈\N{\fs90}someone would put fried onions on the top
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.78,0:28:08.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,也就毁了蛋糕  你就有了一个\N{\fs90}and completely ruin it. You'd have a Victoria sponge
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.64,0:28:10.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,放了洋葱圈的维多利亚海绵蛋糕\N{\fs90}with onion on the top for no reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.75,0:28:13.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 你知道你是个奇葩吧\N{\fs90}James, you know you're weird, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.15,0:28:14.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不叫奇葩 这是这个节目上\N{\fs90}That's not weird. That's the most sensible thing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.87,0:28:16.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,最理智的说法\N{\fs90}that's ever been said on this show.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.15,0:28:17.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你就是奇葩 -奇葩个毛线\N{\fs90}- You are weird. - I'm not weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.98,0:28:19.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,他真的奇葩 就前几天\N{\fs90}He is weird! We were coming through the airport
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.01,0:28:21.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们穿过芝加哥机场\N{\fs90}here the other day, coming through Chicago,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.58,0:28:23.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,他突然说 “杰里米 闻闻我的夹克”\N{\fs90}and he went, "Jeremy, smell my jacket."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.84,0:28:25.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,他说了啥\N{\fs90}- He said what?!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.10,0:28:26.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没错 -我是这么说的\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.24,0:28:27.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,他说“闻闻我夹克” 我说“为啥”\N{\fs90}He said, "Smell my jacket." I said, "Why?"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.75,0:28:30.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,他说“因为它闻起来像旧唱片机”\N{\fs90}He said, "Because it smells of old record players."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.44,0:28:32.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,-伙计 这是真奇葩 -但真的像\N{\fs90}- Mate, that is weird. - But it did!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.91,0:28:35.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,你知道旧唱片机是没有味道的吧\N{\fs90}You know record players don't smell of anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.24,0:28:36.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,有的 旧的那种有\N{\fs90}They do. Old ones do.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.68,0:28:38.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,闻起来就像旧唱片机\N{\fs90}They smell of old record players.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.38,0:28:40.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,谁知道旧唱片机什么味儿\N{\fs90}Who knows what they smell like?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.24,0:28:41.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我想我们要... -腐烂的...\N{\fs90}- I'd like us-- - The decaying...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.35,0:28:42.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉着我们要继续了\N{\fs90}I'd like us to move it on
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.68,0:28:44.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为已经有点诡异了\N{\fs90}because it's getting scary now.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.38,0:28:46.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,和旧唱片机没关系\N{\fs90}That's not the record player!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.44,0:28:47.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,你到底想干嘛\N{\fs90}What are you on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.84,0:28:49.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,有人有旧唱片机吗\N{\fs90}Does anybody have an old record player,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.41,0:28:50.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者任何老旧的电器\N{\fs90}or anything old electrical?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.55,0:28:51.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们有种味道 不是吗\N{\fs90}They smell, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.41,0:28:53.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,有人闻过旧唱片机吗\N{\fs90}Has anybody ever smelled an old record player?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.21,0:28:55.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的吗 你闻过\N{\fs90}Really? You think you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.00,0:28:56.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,你真去闻了旧的...\N{\fs90}You've smelled an old...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.73,0:28:58.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,哎哟我天\N{\fs90}god, strewth!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.27,0:29:03.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,你的旧唱片机带蜡筒嘛\N{\fs90}Did it have a wax cylinder on it, your old record player?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.54,0:29:06.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们闻起来像旧塑料和热橡胶\N{\fs90}They smell like old plastic and warm rubber.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.30,0:29:07.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 就是这个\N{\fs90}Yeah, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.21,0:29:10.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,是不是闻起来像船长的羞羞抽屉\N{\fs90}That smells like his special drawer ,is that.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.81,0:29:13.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,你像是和爱迪生说话啦\N{\fs90}You're actually talking to Thomas Edison there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.95,0:29:18.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,面对面的\N{\fs90}In person.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.35,0:29:19.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,好样的 \N{\fs90}Well done, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.75,0:29:21.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 我们被告知\N{\fs90}Now, as we're told
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.55,0:29:24.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,如今几乎每天\N{\fs90}almost every day these days, really,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.61,0:29:27.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,自然界的珊瑚礁正在不断死亡\N{\fs90}the world's coral reefs are all dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.27,0:29:30.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且人们说是汽车的错\N{\fs90}And we're told that this is the fault of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.70,0:29:32.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,那么 既然我们弄了个汽车节目\N{\fs90}Well, since we host a car show,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.78,0:29:35.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们想这也是我们的责任和义务\N{\fs90}we thought it would be our duty and responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.35,0:29:37.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,来做些什么\N{\fs90}to do something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.34,0:29:48.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,在加勒比海 一切看起来都很好\N{\fs90}Here in the Caribbean, all appears to be well.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.38,0:29:50.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是在潺潺蓝洋之下\N{\fs90}But under the shimmering blue sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.98,0:29:53.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,只是无尽的沙石\N{\fs90}there's just miles and miles of sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.19,0:29:57.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,简直是水下沙漠\N{\fs90}It's an underwater desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.83,0:30:01.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且就算你找到一块礁石\N{\fs90}And even when you do find a reef,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.21,0:30:03.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,大多数珊瑚已经死亡或者濒危\N{\fs90}most of the coral is dead or dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.73,0:30:09.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,三十八年前\N{\fs90}Thirty-eight years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.61,0:30:11.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,当地政府下放了一艘船\N{\fs90}the local government sank a ship
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.47,0:30:13.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,来促进珊瑚生态的恢复\N{\fs90}to encourage the coral to come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.88,0:30:16.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,这奏效了\N{\fs90}And it's working.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.88,0:30:19.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,这已经是一片生命的绿洲\N{\fs90}It's already an oasis of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.82,0:30:25.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,这给了我们一个启发\N{\fs90}And that gave us an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.35,0:30:29.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么要用船来作为珊瑚礁的生存枢纽\N{\fs90}Why use a ship as the hub or your coral reef?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.18,0:30:31.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,为啥不用汽车呢 毕竟有数不尽的车\N{\fs90}Why not use cars? There are millions of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.78,0:30:34.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是我们所做的 我们弄来五辆车\N{\fs90}So that's exactly what we've done. We've got five cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.72,0:30:36.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,并没有走各种\N{\fs90}And rather than go through all the expense
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.61,0:30:38.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,昂贵又复杂的回收过程\N{\fs90}and complication of recycling them,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.30,0:30:40.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,而是直接拆解 把引擎拿掉\N{\fs90}we've stripped them, taken the engines out,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.32,0:30:42.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,去掉车漆 就可以放入海底了\N{\fs90}removed the paint, and they're ready to go in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.84,0:30:44.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,这真的很机智\N{\fs90}This really does make perfect sense,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.01,0:30:46.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为当车子进了水里\N{\fs90}because when the car is in the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.81,0:30:48.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,就会开始溶解腐蚀\N{\fs90}it will start to corrode,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.04,0:30:49.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后吸引各种\N{\fs90}and that attracts all the things
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.32,0:30:50.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,适合珊瑚礁生长的物质\N{\fs90}that help the coral grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.61,0:30:52.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,接着汽车自己锈着锈着\N{\fs90}And then the car itself just rusts away
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.95,0:30:54.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,就锈没了\N{\fs90}to absolutely nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.35,0:30:56.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,比如这一台 它本来\N{\fs90}So this one, which started life
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.38,0:30:57.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,是一台极其糟糕的标致\N{\fs90}as a pretty horrible Peugeot
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.67,0:30:58.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,也永远会是一辆糟糕的车\N{\fs90}and was always a terrible car,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.95,0:31:01.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,但最后却成了一座漂亮的珊瑚礁\N{\fs90}will eventually become a beautiful coral reef.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.72,0:31:04.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且这个过程还挺快\N{\fs90}And all this happens quite quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.41,0:31:05.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,就几年的工夫\N{\fs90}So in just a few years' time,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.70,0:31:08.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,BBC光在车轮拱罩这里\N{\fs90}the BBC will be able to make a wildlife documentary
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.35,0:31:09.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,就能拍一部野生纪录片了\N{\fs90}just in this wheel arch.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.63,0:31:10.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了 我们准备好了车\N{\fs90}Anyway, we've got the cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.86,0:31:12.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,我弄了一台吊车\N{\fs90}I've got a crane.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.44,0:31:14.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,就只差一艘船了\N{\fs90}All we need now is a boat,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.21,0:31:15.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是杰里米的任务\N{\fs90}which is a job we gave to Jeremy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.72,0:31:17.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,是他的责任\N{\fs90}That's his responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.10,0:31:18.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,他肯定要玩脱的\N{\fs90}He'll have overdone it, won't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.17,0:31:20.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,他不一直说要做大么\N{\fs90}Well, he'll have made a statement of some sort, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.94,0:31:23.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,货运舰 扎扎实实的货船\N{\fs90}Freight ship. Full-on freight ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.38,0:31:24.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者油轮\N{\fs90}Or a tanker.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.62,0:31:37.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,他并没有过度\N{\fs90}Oh. He hasn't overdone it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.55,0:31:39.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是他么\N{\fs90}Is that him?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.63,0:31:43.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,这东西意义何在\N{\fs90}What is the point of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.03,0:31:45.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,你能把它绑上岸吗\N{\fs90}Will you come and tie it up?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.64,0:31:53.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我见过最差劲的船 糟糕透顶\N{\fs90} That's the worst boat I've ever seen. That's awful!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.18,0:31:55.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,-它有什么问题吗 -那个....\N{\fs90}- What's the matter with it? - Well, it...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.24,0:31:58.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们给了你5000美元去买艘船\N{\fs90}We gave you $5,000 to buy a boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.61,0:31:59.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,船好贵的\N{\fs90}Boats are expensive!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.98,0:32:02.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,但你绝对没在这破烂上花五千块\N{\fs90}You didn't spend all five grand on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.72,0:32:03.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这不是一艘五千... -没错\N{\fs90} That is not a five thou-- - Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.55,0:32:05.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,我牙痛 不要这么凶\N{\fs90}I've got toothache. Be kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.70,0:32:08.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,毫不相关 这就不是一艘五千块的船\N{\fs90}Irrelevant. That is not a $5,000 boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.04,0:32:09.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,-它真的是- 这都不能叫船 你自己看\N{\fs90}- It is! - It's barely a boat. Look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.07,0:32:11.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,这很棒的 你能放一辆车在这里\N{\fs90}It's brilliant! You'll get a car on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.99,0:32:14.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,-哪里 -放在后舱\N{\fs90}- Er... Where? - On the back!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.78,0:32:16.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你从哪儿买来的 -某汉子\N{\fs90}- Who did you buy it from? - A man.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.30,0:32:18.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,-卖的时候他在偷笑吧 - 并没有\N{\fs90}- Was he laughing? - No, he wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.66,0:32:20.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我能登船吗 -不能\N{\fs90}- Can I come aboard? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.70,0:32:22.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,它应该装不下两个\N{\fs90}I don't think it can take two.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.94,0:32:25.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,看吧 这也太差了\N{\fs90} Look! It's terrible!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.67,0:32:26.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,与其站在那儿\N{\fs90}Instead of just standing there,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.70,0:32:28.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,对一个牙疼的人一顿乱批\N{\fs90}criticising a man who's got toothache,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.31,0:32:32.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,你为何不吊一辆车来\N{\fs90}why don't you go and get a car on the crane
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.27,0:32:33.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,开始装货\N{\fs90}and start loading it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.48,0:32:40.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快 我们的第一辆车准备装船了\N{\fs90}Soon, our first car was ready to be lifted onto the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.45,0:32:43.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,回馈自然感觉真好\N{\fs90}It's just nice to be putting something back, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.02,0:32:45.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的 这是一台小欧宝Corsa\N{\fs90}It genuinely is. It's a little old Corsa,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.61,0:32:46.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,即将被珊瑚覆盖\N{\fs90}and it's gonna be full of coral.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.79,0:32:48.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,珊瑚先生驾到 游过来\N{\fs90}Mr Coral coming, swimming along.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.92,0:32:50.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 这里有一个能落脚的玩东西\N{\fs90}"Ooh, there's something to latch on to."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.70,0:32:52.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,接着他的伙伴也过来\N{\fs90}Then his friend comes along.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.15,0:32:54.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,这点子实在太棒了\N{\fs90}This is a genuinely brilliant idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.21,0:32:55.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,但那边并没有让我...\N{\fs90}That doesn't fill me with...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.77,0:32:57.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,信心爆棚\N{\fs90}total confidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.71,0:33:05.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,往下一点 往下\N{\fs90}Down a bit! Down!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.81,0:33:07.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,你必须...\N{\fs90}You'll have to...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.78,0:33:09.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,往外一点\N{\fs90}Boom out!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.28,0:33:11.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是“往外”的姿势吗\N{\fs90}Is that the sign for "boom out"?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.02,0:33:13.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是啊\N{\fs90} That. Yeah, that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.79,0:33:16.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,像是在被原始人指挥一样\N{\fs90}It's like being guided by The Village People.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.41,0:33:18.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,挺顺利的 除非...\N{\fs90}It's working now. Unless--
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.12,0:33:19.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,往上提\N{\fs90}On! On!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.99,0:33:22.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,-接下来的危险...-你真是帮上了忙\N{\fs90}- The next danger-- - You're really helping.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.35,0:33:24.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我拿着导向绳的 - 行 快去\N{\fs90}- I've got the guideline. - Right, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.67,0:33:33.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-詹姆斯 往下一点 -小心来风\N{\fs90}Down a bit, James. - Watch for the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.84,0:33:35.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 你能把它换个方向嘛\N{\fs90}Hammond, can you swing it around?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.84,0:33:36.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,你想转一下吗\N{\fs90}Do you want me to swing it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.64,0:33:37.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 你试试看\N{\fs90}Yeah, try and get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.98,0:33:39.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,卧槽\N{\fs90}Oh, shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.18,0:33:42.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,谁拉了那根绳子\N{\fs90} Who pulled that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.82,0:33:46.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们必须救车 那可是珊瑚礁啊 救它\N{\fs90}We've got to save the car! It's a reef! Save it!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.61,0:33:48.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,完了 它沉了 没救了\N{\fs90}Oh, it's gone! It's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.22,0:33:49.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,谁拉了...\N{\fs90}Who pulled the...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.62,0:33:52.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是用来释放的 你个呆木脑壳\N{\fs90}That's to release it, you Muppet!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.21,0:33:54.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,我以为那是个导向绳\N{\fs90}Well, I thought it was a guide rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.10,0:33:57.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 我来导向 你只要等它到船上然后释放\N{\fs90}No, I steer it! You just release it when it's on there!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.55,0:33:58.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,他让我来导向的\N{\fs90}He told me to steer it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.81,0:34:00.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,他说 拉那个绳子来控制\N{\fs90}He said, "Pull the rope to steer it."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.81,0:34:02.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,这可是一辆40万英镑的起重机\N{\fs90}This is a £400,000 crane!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.90,0:34:04.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,为啥你要用一根绳子来调方向\N{\fs90}Why would you steer it with a piece of string?!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.78,0:34:06.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,这儿不是有了这些握把和按钮么\N{\fs90}It's got all these knobs and buttons.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.18,0:34:09.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,我来操纵 你来释放\N{\fs90}I steer it, you release it!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.04,0:34:11.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以那是快速释放?\N{\fs90}So that's a quick release?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.01,0:34:12.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,-没错 -懂了\N{\fs90}- Yes! - Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.42,0:34:18.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我说我们只有四辆车怎么样\N{\fs90}What if we just said we only had four cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.75,0:34:21.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们就准备了四辆车 拿掉了引擎\N{\fs90}So we've taken four cars, removed the engines
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.92,0:34:23.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,去掉了车漆 随时准备进入海底\N{\fs90}and the paint, and they're ready to go in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.90,0:34:26.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们再对着摄像机来一遍 -好的 好的\N{\fs90}- We'll do that piece to camera again. - Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.23,0:34:29.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,关键在于 为什么要用船来作为珊瑚礁的生存枢纽\N{\fs90}The thing is, why use a ship as the hub of your reef?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.70,0:34:31.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,为啥不用汽车呢 毕竟有数不尽的车\N{\fs90}Why not use cars? There are millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.27,0:34:34.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们就准备了四辆车 拿掉了引擎\N{\fs90}So we've taken four cars, removed the engines,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.78,0:34:38.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,扒光之后 就做好放入海底的准备了\N{\fs90}stripped them down and they're ready to go in the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.10,0:34:40.12,字幕,,0,0,0,, 然后詹姆斯...对\N{\fs90}And then James... Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.18,0:34:41.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后... 然后...\N{\fs90}And then... And then,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.41,0:34:43.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆标致不是什么好车\N{\fs90}this Peugeot was no good as a car,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.54,0:34:47.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是珊瑚会生长在上面\N{\fs90}but will be... but the coral will just stick to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.05,0:34:49.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,和海藻一起慢慢氧化\N{\fs90}oxidising and algae.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.18,0:34:50.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,用不了多久的\N{\fs90}Doesn't take very long.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.05,0:34:53.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,BBC会拍一部纪录片 轮拱什么的\N{\fs90}One day, BBC documentary, wheel arch.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.58,0:34:56.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,是啊 只用了四辆车 就这些\N{\fs90}Yeah, from just four cars. That's all we had.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.41,0:34:57.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,只需要四辆车就能形成珊瑚礁\N{\fs90}Four cars. That's all you need for a reef.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.41,0:34:59.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了 这是我们选的船\N{\fs90}Right, here's the boat we've selected.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.30,0:35:00.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,稍微有点破损\N{\fs90}It's a little bit damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.26,0:35:04.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,把释放绳放在一边之后\N{\fs90}With the release rope stowed,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.32,0:35:06.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们把四辆车中的第一辆弄上了船\N{\fs90}we managed to get the first of our four cars
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.87,0:35:10.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,船的顶部本来就是破损的\N{\fs90}onto the boat, which had come with a broken roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.94,0:35:13.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 很好\N{\fs90}Yeah. Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.94,0:35:16.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,-就是这样  -超棒\N{\fs90}- Yes! - Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.21,0:35:18.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,很好 搞定了\N{\fs90}Good! Result.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.98,0:35:21.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后我们得把它固定住\N{\fs90}And then we had to secure it in place.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.08,0:35:26.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,我搞不懂这些棘轮带\N{\fs90}I don't understand ratchet straps.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.81,0:35:30.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,那个 船里进水了\N{\fs90}Er... There's water coming into the boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.35,0:35:33.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,-不 我买的时候里面就有水  -船漏了\N{\fs90}- No, there was some in when I bought it. - It's leaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.15,0:35:35.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,舱底总归有点水的\N{\fs90}There's always a bit of water in the bilges.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.72,0:35:37.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以船上才会配舱底泵\N{\fs90}It's why boats have bilge pumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.66,0:35:39.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 水涌进来了\N{\fs90}No, it's coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.37,0:35:42.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是流进来 而是涌进来了\N{\fs90}It's not just like it's in, it's coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.75,0:35:45.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,-但我这没有 -这有洞 船在漏水\N{\fs90}- Well, there's none here. - There's holes! It's leaking!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.58,0:35:48.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,糟糕 的确有洞 快把我们拴在吊车上\N{\fs90}Oh, shit! No, there is! Well, attach us to the crane.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.44,0:35:50.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,呃 船在下沉\N{\fs90}Er... It's gone down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.61,0:35:52.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,它在 它要沉了\N{\fs90}It has gone... It is going down.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.21,0:35:54.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果把我们栓在吊车上\N{\fs90}If you attach us to the crane,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.21,0:35:55.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,它就不会沉了 对吧\N{\fs90}it won't sink, will it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.22,0:35:56.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们绑好了\N{\fs90}We're tied on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.55,0:35:59.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 你能拉一下吗\N{\fs90}James, can you just take the slack?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.52,0:36:02.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,可惜 詹姆斯误解了\N{\fs90}Sadly, James misunderstood
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.98,0:36:04.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个简单的指令\N{\fs90}this simple instruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.27,0:36:06.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 船尾这边要塌了\N{\fs90}Oh, the whole thing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.04,0:36:07.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,整艘船都要翻了\N{\fs90}has collapsed at the back!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.47,0:36:08.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 我的天\N{\fs90}Oh, dear God!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.46,0:36:10.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,等一下 停 怎么回事\N{\fs90}Wait! Stop! Whoa! Whoa! What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.36,0:36:11.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,船要翻了\N{\fs90}It's falling over!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.83,0:36:13.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 船要翻了\N{\fs90}James, it's falling!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.43,0:36:15.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你们想怎么样  -我的天呐\N{\fs90}- What do you want? - Holy Mother of God!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.78,0:36:18.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,船要沉了 弃船自保\N{\fs90}It's going down! Abandon ship! Save yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.14,0:36:23.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,拉住啊 詹姆斯\N{\fs90}Catch it, James!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.68,0:36:25.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,救船\N{\fs90}Save it!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.45,0:36:26.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,别\N{\fs90}Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.71,0:36:28.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,你搞什么呢\N{\fs90}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.65,0:36:30.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 我的天\N{\fs90}Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.42,0:36:32.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,法国特勤局\N{\fs90}The French Secret Service
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.52,0:36:36.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,干的活都没这么好\N{\fs90}didn't do a job as good as this.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.16,0:36:38.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不想跟你们说话\N{\fs90}I'm not talking to any of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.24,0:36:40.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,别啊 拜托 这是船长的错\N{\fs90}No. Come on, it was May's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.41,0:36:41.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,是你买的这艘破船\N{\fs90}You bought a crap boat,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.58,0:36:43.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,也是你让那只长毛狗开吊车\N{\fs90}you put an idiot spaniel on the crane,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.44,0:36:45.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有 想想我们\N{\fs90}and, also, think what we were gonna do
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.81,0:36:46.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,本该赋予这辆车的使命\N{\fs90}for the conception of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.95,0:36:49.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,人们会喜爱它\N{\fs90}People would love the car. They would see it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.32,0:36:51.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,把它看作珊瑚的完美栖息地\N{\fs90}as a friendly, coral-loving thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.37,0:36:53.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,你游起来像个老太太\N{\fs90}You're swimming like an old woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.61,0:36:55.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,我他妈不想待在这水里\N{\fs90}I don't like being in the bloody water!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.84,0:37:00.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的 我很不爽 我是伯明翰人\N{\fs90}Fact! I'm not comfortable! I'm from Birmingham!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.45,0:37:03.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,在邮轮经常停靠的位置\N{\fs90}Having sunk a boat and two cars
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.21,0:37:04.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,沉了一艘船和两辆车之后\N{\fs90}where the cruise liners normally park,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.07,0:37:08.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,港口管理者建议我们滚蛋\N{\fs90}the port authorities suggested we go away.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.82,0:37:12.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们带着剩下的三辆车\N{\fs90}So we took our three remaining cars
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.53,0:37:13.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,去了附近的一个码头\N{\fs90}to a nearby marina,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.99,0:37:15.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,自己造了一个筏子\N{\fs90}built ourselves a raft,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.50,0:37:16.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后租了一艘\N{\fs90}and hired a boat
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.98,0:37:18.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,船头有吊车的船\N{\fs90}which had a crane on the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.20,0:37:24.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,-船长  -什么事\N{\fs90}- May! - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.98,0:37:26.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,你别开吊车了\N{\fs90}You're not operating the crane.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.97,0:37:29.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,你来开\N{\fs90}You are operating the crane.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.24,0:37:30.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,行\N{\fs90}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.28,0:37:31.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,我就想说明一点\N{\fs90}I'd just like to point out
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.48,0:37:33.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,这份工作我做得很好\N{\fs90}that I've been fired from a job
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.21,0:37:34.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我被开除了\N{\fs90}that I was doing perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.38,0:37:36.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,我故意的\N{\fs90}Meant that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.78,0:37:39.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,这吊车不动啊 是不是哪里有个开关\N{\fs90}I can't get the crane working. Is there a switch?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.24,0:37:41.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,别问我 我不会开吊车\N{\fs90}Don't come to me for help. I'm rubbish at cranes.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.75,0:37:44.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,我也没问你啊 谁说我要问你了\N{\fs90}I didn't, did I? Did I?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.42,0:37:47.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快 我们就准备装第一辆车了\N{\fs90}Soon, we were ready to load our first car.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.93,0:37:50.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,你差着十万八千里呢\N{\fs90}You're miles away!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.00,0:37:51.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,你得放到正上方\N{\fs90}You've got to be spot-on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.38,0:37:52.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,我只能举到这儿\N{\fs90}I can only lift it to there.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.57,0:37:54.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,这边 往这边点\N{\fs90}This way, this way, this way, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.80,0:37:56.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 往上\N{\fs90}No, up, up, up.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.84,0:37:59.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,我没法 杰里米 你要往后退\N{\fs90}I can't... Jeremy, you'll have to go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.58,0:38:01.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,你的船一直在动 我也没办法啊\N{\fs90}I can't do it if you keep moving the boat!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.92,0:38:04.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果要后退 应该是往那边\N{\fs90}If I want to go backwards, I should go that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.08,0:38:06.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,对 这边 你要到 我这里动不了\N{\fs90}Right, this way. You've got to... I can't move it...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.01,0:38:08.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,我够不到 他在开船\N{\fs90}I can't go that way! He's driving!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.21,0:38:09.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我动不了啊\N{\fs90}I can't move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.52,0:38:11.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们为什么不 噢天哪\N{\fs90}Why don't we pick it... Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.65,0:38:15.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们往哪儿走呢\N{\fs90}Where are we going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.72,0:38:18.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,该怪的是 风一直在乱吹\N{\fs90}The bad things... It's the wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.39,0:38:20.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们怎么在这儿\N{\fs90}Why are we over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.75,0:38:21.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,有风\N{\fs90}Wind!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.59,0:38:24.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,来了 就这样\N{\fs90}Here he comes! This is it! This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.33,0:38:26.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,不偏不倚\N{\fs90}We're coming in hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.37,0:38:28.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,停 别用这钩子追我\N{\fs90}Stop... chasing me with the bloody crane!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.38,0:38:29.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长 你这辈子就不能有一件事干得麻利点吗\N{\fs90}May, will you do something quickly in your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.95,0:38:31.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,我真想杀了他\N{\fs90}I'm going to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.97,0:38:35.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,有了 好的 快拉走\N{\fs90}Here we go! Yes! Run away! Run away!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.61,0:38:37.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们成功了\N{\fs90}We have hooked the apple!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.68,0:38:41.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,-一点点来  -我们真棒\N{\fs90}-In a bit, in a bit. -We are good.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.68,0:38:44.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们太棒了 这简直是奇迹\N{\fs90}We are so good, it's almost incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.35,0:38:48.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在我们轻车熟路了\N{\fs90}Now we had our eye in...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.36,0:38:52.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 我的天\N{\fs90}Oh, Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.33,0:38:56.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,装第二辆车易如反掌\N{\fs90}...loading the second car was the work of a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.60,0:38:58.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,-勾上了  -天哪 真棒\N{\fs90}-We're on. -Oh, my God! Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.17,0:39:02.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,行了 可以了\N{\fs90}That's it. That'll do.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.47,0:39:05.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我做过的最有男子气概的事了\N{\fs90}This is the manliest thing I've ever done.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.97,0:39:08.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要把我大蛋蛋放在我吊车上\N{\fs90}I'm just gonna rest my big balls on my crane.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.08,0:39:16.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,筏子装满了\N{\fs90}With our raft full,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.42,0:39:17.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们出发前往\N{\fs90}we headed out to the spot
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.04,0:39:20.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,经海洋生物专家鉴定\N{\fs90}identified by marine biologists
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.02,0:39:24.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,拥有最适宜珊瑚礁形成的\N{\fs90}as having the perfect depth, current and temperature
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.09,0:39:25.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,完美水深 洋流和温度之地\N{\fs90}for a reef to form.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.19,0:39:28.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,放下暗礁\N{\fs90}Release the reef!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.73,0:39:31.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好的  -搞定\N{\fs90}-Yes! -There it goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.03,0:39:33.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,-暗礁诞生了  -那是我们的暗礁\N{\fs90}- The reef is born! -That's our reef!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.33,0:39:35.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,-沉下去吧  -来吧 珊瑚\N{\fs90}- Sink! - Come, coral! Come!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.34,0:39:41.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,-下去吧  -好棒\N{\fs90}-Go! -Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.44,0:39:44.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,我非常满意\N{\fs90}Oh, I'm pleased with that!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.34,0:39:46.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆标致206\N{\fs90}The Peugeot 206.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.51,0:39:47.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,太棒了\N{\fs90}That is brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.02,0:39:52.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,接下来 我要把车锚到位\N{\fs90}Next, we had to anchor the cars in place,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.92,0:39:56.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我们三个之中 唯一有资格的潜水员的任务\N{\fs90}which was a job for the only qualified diver among us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.59,0:39:58.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且他还自带了装备\N{\fs90}He'd even brought his own equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.49,0:40:02.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 往后一点\N{\fs90}Right. Back a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.26,0:40:03.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,往后 碰到我鼻子了\N{\fs90}Back... That's on my nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.84,0:40:04.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,别叫唤了\N{\fs90}Stop moaning!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.08,0:40:19.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果他是心脏外科医生\N{\fs90}If he were a heart surgeon,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.70,0:40:21.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,他会带着一个旧皮包出现\N{\fs90}he would turn up with an old leather bag
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.52,0:40:23.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,包里有一把锯一把锤子\N{\fs90}with a saw and hammer in it, wouldn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.24,0:40:25.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,我来了 准备进行手术\N{\fs90}"I'm ready to do your operation. Here I am."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.29,0:40:32.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,就像一张旧桌子 上面还有个老式胶木电话\N{\fs90}It's like his old table with his Bakelite telephone on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.61,0:40:34.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的  -你好 翰墨史密斯37号\N{\fs90}- Yes. - "Hello. Hammersmith 37 here."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.46,0:40:38.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯的潜水服太旧了\N{\fs90}James's suit was so old,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.84,0:40:41.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有配备氧气瓶 所以麻烦的是\N{\fs90}it didn't come with air tanks, so, annoyingly,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.84,0:40:44.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们要负责让他活着\N{\fs90}it was our responsibility to keep him alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.51,0:40:48.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们要干多久\N{\fs90}How long have we got to do this for?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.77,0:40:51.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,一直到他干完活吧\N{\fs90}Well, for as long as he's done there.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.18,0:40:53.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-说真的 累死我了  -我有点晕\N{\fs90}- Honestly, I'm exhausted. - I'm getting dizzy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.21,0:40:56.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们应该继续\N{\fs90}We should keep going.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.85,0:40:58.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 你看 那里有个发电机\N{\fs90}No. Look, there's a generator.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.92,0:41:00.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们为何不把它连上发电机呢\N{\fs90}Why don't we just connect it to the generator?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.13,0:41:09.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,快点\N{\fs90}Now. Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.29,0:41:11.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,-知道了  -你个白痴\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - You're an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.38,0:41:18.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,救命的空气来了\N{\fs90}Life-saving air.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.04,0:41:20.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,这样就行了\N{\fs90}Oh, there we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.94,0:41:23.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,搞定 我们去找点乐子吧\N{\fs90}On. And relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.62,0:41:27.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,加油啊 机器\N{\fs90} come on machine
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.99,0:41:43.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,就差一点点\N{\fs90}Nearly!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.39,0:42:13.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,回话 船长\N{\fs90}Come in, James.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.73,0:42:16.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,当我们的同事最终浮出水面\N{\fs90}When our colleague finally surfaced...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.80,0:42:18.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,他非常生气\N{\fs90}he was very angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.67,0:42:22.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,我根本就不在车附近 差得远了\N{\fs90}That was nowhere near the cars. Nowhere near.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.97,0:42:25.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么不在车的附近\N{\fs90}What was nowhere near the cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.18,0:42:26.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,你不如把我放在洛杉矶的海岸上\N{\fs90}You might as well have dropped me off the coast of Los Angeles!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.98,0:42:29.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我根本看不见  -别说了\N{\fs90}- I couldn't even see them! - Just stop. Stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.54,0:42:31.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,你什么意思\N{\fs90}What do you... What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.14,0:42:33.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,你怎么会 你总是不停地说\N{\fs90}How did you manage... You're the boat expert,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.47,0:42:34.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,你是船舶专家\N{\fs90}as you're forever telling us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.64,0:42:36.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,你是怎么做到在这儿放下车\N{\fs90}How did you manage to put the cars there
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.30,0:42:39.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后把船开出去90米的\N{\fs90}and then move the boat about 100 yards away?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.41,0:42:40.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,-它自己漂走的  -漂走了一点\N{\fs90}- We drifted. - We drifted a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.18,0:42:42.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你的任务完成了吗  -没有\N{\fs90}- Have you done the job? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.66,0:42:45.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,-什么  -车没有被锚住\N{\fs90}- What? - The cars are not anchored.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.12,0:42:46.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为我刚一到车那儿\N{\fs90}Because when I got there,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.50,0:42:49.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,你这四处乱漂的愚蠢的橙色罐头皮小船\N{\fs90}your drifting, stupid, orange biscuit-tin boat
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.67,0:42:51.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,就把我拉走了\N{\fs90}yanked me back off it!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.04,0:42:52.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们没有一整个下午的时间\N{\fs90}We don't have an afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.58,0:42:54.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,让你一边划桨一边浪费\N{\fs90}to just throw away while you go paddling.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.58,0:42:56.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,你是说 我得去完成任务 不是吗\N{\fs90}You're saying... I'm gonna have to do it, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.54,0:43:02.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快 詹姆斯邦德准备下水了\N{\fs90}Soon, James Bond was ready to go in the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.71,0:43:06.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我看上去像罗杰摩尔吗  -像\N{\fs90}- Do I look like Roger Moore? - Yeah, you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.88,0:43:09.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,-特别像  -像那个卖菜的罗杰摩尔\N{\fs90}- You do, yeah. Yeah. - Roger Moore, the greengrocer.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.75,0:43:13.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,-下去吧  -耶\N{\fs90}- Let go. Yes! - Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.25,0:43:16.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,我刚给了杰里米一把焊枪\N{\fs90}I've just handed Jeremy a welding iron.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.42,0:43:17.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 我的天\N{\fs90}Oh, dear God.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.63,0:43:25.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不是很相信杰里米的焊接水平\N{\fs90}I'm not sure I trust Jeremy to do welding.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.77,0:43:27.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,我连他会去网上看\N{\fs90}I wouldn't trust Jeremy
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.87,0:43:31.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,焊接教程都不信\N{\fs90}to watch a YouTube guide to welding.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.17,0:43:34.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,-噢  -怎么了\N{\fs90}-Oh! -What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.31,0:43:36.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-出事了  -杰里米\N{\fs90}-That's gone wrong. -Jeremy?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.81,0:43:38.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,出了相当可怕的事\N{\fs90}Badly, horribly wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.15,0:43:49.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,-怎么样了  -非常好\N{\fs90}- How did that go? - Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.59,0:43:50.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是吗  -当然\N{\fs90}- Did it? - Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.26,0:44:02.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们回到岸上 吃了顿庆功宴\N{\fs90}We headed back to shore for an agreeable dinner,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.67,0:44:05.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,很庆幸我们重要的环保工作\N{\fs90}happy that our important environmental work
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.47,0:44:07.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,最终还是顺利完成\N{\fs90}was, at last, going well.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.08,0:44:15.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是珊瑚开始长了吗\N{\fs90}But are the coral starting now?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.88,0:44:18.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是的  -所以它们就在水下\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - So they're down there now.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.10,0:44:20.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,-一小块珊瑚会... -是的 会长成的\N{\fs90}- A bit of coral's gonna... - Yeah, it will have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.92,0:44:22.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是很大的珊瑚礁\N{\fs90}It's not a big coral reef,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.75,0:44:24.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这是珊瑚礁的开始\N{\fs90}but it's the start of a coral reef.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.52,0:44:26.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,好样的 伙计们 我们做到了\N{\fs90}Well done, chaps. We have done...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.52,0:44:28.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们知道我不碰杯的\N{\fs90}I don't clink glasses, as you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.21,0:44:30.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,但让我们为今天的成就举杯\N{\fs90}but we can raise a glass to our success today.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.47,0:44:31.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 我们干得好\N{\fs90}Yes. Well done, us.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.10,0:44:37.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,可能这就是大众在做的\N{\fs90}Maybe that's what Volkswagen were doing--
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.07,0:44:38.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,造一片珊瑚礁\N{\fs90}building a reef.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.38,0:44:40.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,很有可能\N{\fs90}That could be it. That could be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.31,0:44:44.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,稍后继续我们重要的海洋生物工作\N{\fs90}We're gonna pick up our important marine biology work later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.50,0:44:48.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在是明星脑碰脑环节\N{\fs90}But now it's time to play Celebrity Brain Crash!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.55,0:44:57.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,这没法更好了\N{\fs90}That doesn't get any better.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.24,0:44:59.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,这片头 真的没法做更好了\N{\fs90}That really doesn't get any better, that sting.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.41,0:45:02.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,但无论如何 今晚的嘉宾来自\N{\fs90}But anyway, my guest tonight is from...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.41,0:45:04.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,这要怎么形容呢\N{\fs90}Well, how can I describe it, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.18,0:45:05.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,世界上第二大\N{\fs90}...the second biggest
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.75,0:45:07.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,也是最重要的 \N{\fs90}and most important part of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.47,0:45:10.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,音乐重镇 英格兰东北\N{\fs90}as far as music is concerned: the Northeast of England.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.98,0:45:12.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 拜托\N{\fs90}Oh, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.24,0:45:13.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,怎么了\N{\fs90}Well, hello?!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.71,0:45:15.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,马克·诺弗勒 保罗·罗杰斯\N{\fs90}Mark Knopfler, Paul Rodgers,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.04,0:45:18.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,戈登·斯汀 小混混乐队的几个妹子\N{\fs90}Gordon Sting, a couple of people out of Little Mix.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.78,0:45:21.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,-林迪斯芳 很棒  -嗯 林迪斯芳 我们先跳过\N{\fs90}- Lindisfarne. Mm, lovely. - Yes, Lindisfarne. We'll gloss over that.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.64,0:45:24.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,但我们也有核心人物\N{\fs90}But then we've also got... the main man.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.30,0:45:27.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们把他带来了 他是世界上最大的摇滚乐队\N{\fs90}The man we have lined up for you, he is the lead singer
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.69,0:45:30.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,AC/DC的主唱\N{\fs90}of the biggest rock band in the world, AC/DC.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.69,0:45:33.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,女士们先生们 布莱恩·约翰逊\N{\fs90}Ladies and gentlemen, Brian Johnson!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.99,0:45:36.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,他在那儿\N{\fs90}- There he is! - There he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.60,0:45:38.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,他在那儿 他来了\N{\fs90}There he is! Here he comes!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.50,0:45:40.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们要跟他聊什么呢\N{\fs90}What are we gonna talk to him about?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.90,0:45:43.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他开始尝试赛车运动了  -是啊\N{\fs90}- Well, he's taken up motor racing. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.17,0:45:45.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他有个新的电视节目  -对 在路上\N{\fs90}- He's got a new TV show. - Yes, on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.67,0:45:47.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,他在路上\N{\fs90}He's on the road.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.07,0:45:49.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,我要跟他聊聊 他在世界最顶端\N{\fs90}I'm gonna talk to him about being at the front
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.35,0:45:50.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,摇滚乐队担任主唱的感受\N{\fs90}of the world's biggest rock band.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.92,0:45:52.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,等等他在哪儿\N{\fs90}- Where is he? - Hang on, where is he
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.71,0:45:54.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他来了  -他在那儿\N{\fs90}- Here he comes! - Oh, there he is!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.87,0:45:57.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,-就在那儿  -是他本人 一个传奇\N{\fs90}- There he is. - The man himself. What a legend!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.55,0:46:00.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,我一直想见见他 我太激动了\N{\fs90}I can't... I've always wanted to meet him. I'm thrilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.12,0:46:01.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,-是啊  -那是一个传奇\N{\fs90}- Yeah. - That is a legend. Proper...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.72,0:46:03.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,-等一下  -哦不\N{\fs90}- Oh, hello. - Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.16,0:46:04.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,-什么  -我的天\N{\fs90}- What? - Oh, my...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.33,0:46:07.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的天呐\N{\fs90}Oh, God!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.26,0:46:13.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们害死了他  -我们害死了布莱恩·约翰逊\N{\fs90}-We killed him. - We've killed Brian Johnson.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.30,0:46:15.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,那真是...\N{\fs90}That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.43,0:46:17.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\fs90}OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.60,0:46:19.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,布莱恩·约翰逊被一群\N{\fs90}Brian Johnson has been run over
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.67,0:46:22.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,以为自己在踢足球的人碾过去了\N{\fs90}by some people who think they are playing football.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.70,0:46:24.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这不是足球 不是吗\N{\fs90}But they're not. It's not football, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.95,0:46:28.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,那不是足球\N{\fs90}That's not football.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.07,0:46:30.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,只是一群穿奇装异服的人\N{\fs90}That's just people dressing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.62,0:46:33.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,-那是... -我们才踢足球\N{\fs90}- That's... - We play football.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.70,0:46:35.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们踢足球  -嗯 用脚\N{\fs90}- We play football. - Yeah, with our feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.64,0:46:36.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,那才是足球\N{\fs90}That is football.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.98,0:46:39.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,-那叫皮球  -啥\N{\fs90}- Soccer! It's soccer! - What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.78,0:46:41.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不是皮球 我们踢的是足球\N{\fs90}It's not soccer! It's football that we play!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.58,0:46:45.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,世界上67.5亿人都叫它足球\N{\fs90}It's 6.75 billion people in the world call it football!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.47,0:46:48.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,随你们怎么抱怨\N{\fs90}You can moan and shout all you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.81,0:46:50.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,事实是 我们是英国人 我们做的节目\N{\fs90}The fact is, we're British and we edit this show,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.75,0:46:52.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们都会被剪掉的\N{\fs90}and you'll just get cut out.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.07,0:46:56.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是个橄榄球\N{\fs90}This is a rugby ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.10,0:46:57.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,看大屏幕\N{\fs90}Look on the screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.30,0:46:58.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们只是在用\N{\fs90}They're only playing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.64,0:47:00.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们的胸肌玩的这个\N{\fs90}with the padding they were born with!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.81,0:47:02.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,这不是足球\N{\fs90}This is not a football!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.51,0:47:04.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,这些人叫他足球\N{\fs90}They call it football.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.25,0:47:12.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,美利坚 美利坚\N{\fs90}USA! USA! USA! USA! USA!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.83,0:47:16.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以...\N{\fs90}So...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.20,0:47:19.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,刚刚踩踏布莱恩·约翰逊的是\N{\fs90}Brian Johnson has been run over by erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.46,0:47:22.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,一些极其勇敢和天才的足球球员\N{\fs90}...some supremely brave and talented footballers.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.67,0:47:31.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是不是说他来不了了\N{\fs90}Does that mean he's not coming on, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.91,0:47:34.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 他被压扁到\N{\fs90}Well, James, he's been hammered
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.27,0:47:35.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,可以塞进信封的厚度\N{\fs90}to the thickness of an envelope
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.61,0:47:38.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的脊柱变成拼图了 所以他来不了\N{\fs90}and his spine is now a jigsaw, so that is a no.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.52,0:47:39.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\fs90}Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.52,0:47:41.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 那我们怎么填补这时间呢\N{\fs90}Right, so what are we gonna do to fill the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.82,0:47:42.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,我没想法\N{\fs90}I've got nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.82,0:47:44.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们可以返回到\N{\fs90}We could get back
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.09,0:47:45.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们重要的海洋生态工作中\N{\fs90}to our important marine biology work.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.89,0:47:47.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好计划 执行  -好的 就这么做\N{\fs90}- Plan. Do it. - Yes, let's do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.59,0:47:49.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以当我们离开时\N{\fs90}So when we left the action,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.06,0:47:51.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我成功的\N{\fs90}I'd successfully
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.23,0:47:53.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,焊接了两辆车到海底\N{\fs90}welded two cars to the seabed,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.60,0:47:55.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,这很好\N{\fs90}and that was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.03,0:47:57.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 我们在第二天采取了行动\N{\fs90}Yeah, and we pick up the action the next day,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.84,0:48:00.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们回去完成这项工作\N{\fs90}as we go back to finish the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.44,0:48:05.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,当我们打算进行最后一辆车的时候\N{\fs90}On our way to get the last car,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.91,0:48:07.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在礁石处停了一会\N{\fs90}we stopped at the reef site
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.28,0:48:09.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,来确保一切都进行顺利\N{\fs90}to make sure everything was OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.28,0:48:12.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,汤姆·戴利\N{\fs90}Tom Daley!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.86,0:48:21.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不喜欢这个\N{\fs90}I don't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.49,0:48:23.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦哦\N{\fs90}Oh. Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.20,0:48:28.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,在水里待了几分钟之后\N{\fs90}And after a few moments in the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.87,0:48:31.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们发现并不顺利\N{\fs90}we discovered it wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.67,0:48:34.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,那些玩意在哪里 浮标在这里\N{\fs90}Where the bloody hell are they? There's the buoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.87,0:48:36.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是这个地方\N{\fs90}This is the wrong place.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.44,0:48:38.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 那个标记了地点\N{\fs90}Yes, that marks the spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.35,0:48:40.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们就是不在这里\N{\fs90}They're just not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.15,0:48:43.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么我们会相信你能把它们安置好\N{\fs90}Why did we trust you to fix them in place?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.67,0:48:45.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我没有 听着 -所有人\N{\fs90}- I didn't... Listen. - Of all people.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.81,0:48:47.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 我不能理解\N{\fs90}Well, I don't understand it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.49,0:48:49.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,我一般不会搞得一团糟\N{\fs90}cos I don't normally make a mess of...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.70,0:48:51.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦这个工作你肯定干的很好\N{\fs90}Oh, you must have made a good job of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.49,0:48:52.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么它们都没了\N{\fs90}That's why they've gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.52,0:48:54.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是证据 或者很多证据\N{\fs90}There is evidence, or a lack of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.72,0:48:56.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,来证明你不会焊接\N{\fs90}to suggest you can't weld.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.01,0:48:58.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,-卧槽 -可能是条鲨鱼\N{\fs90}- Oh, shit. - Maybe a shark...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.78,0:49:00.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,-恩 -什么\N{\fs90}- Er... - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.13,0:49:02.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,-怎么了 -看\N{\fs90}- What? - Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.60,0:49:04.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦太好了\N{\fs90}Oh, brilliant!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.17,0:49:06.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们是怎么做到的\N{\fs90} How the hell did they do that, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.30,0:49:08.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,你感觉到推着我们走的洋流没\N{\fs90}You know this current that's whizzing us about?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.98,0:49:11.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,看它们 一点没有要变礁石的样子 对吧\N{\fs90}Look at them! They're not gonna make a reef, are they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.61,0:49:13.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者 也许它们可以\N{\fs90}Well, maybe it could be
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.98,0:49:15.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,变成一个贵宾们的玩乐之所\N{\fs90}like a play area for the privileged.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.65,0:49:16.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,一堆生锈的车\N{\fs90}Some rusty cars?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.92,0:49:17.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,那个不起作用对吗\N{\fs90}That doesn't work, does it?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.92,0:49:18.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然不\N{\fs90}OTHERS: No.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.12,0:49:24.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,显然 我们要回收它们\N{\fs90}Obviously, we had to retrieve them,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.67,0:49:26.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就意味着把木筏\N{\fs90}which meant moving the raft
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.18,0:49:28.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,移到起重船的船尾\N{\fs90}to the stern of our crane boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.23,0:49:32.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯 你把那头松开了吗\N{\fs90}James, have you untied that end?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.03,0:49:36.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 准备好接住绳子 来了\N{\fs90}Yeah. Get ready to catch this rope. Here we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.44,0:49:38.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,把它拉过来点 整整齐\N{\fs90}Pull it along a bit and get it sort of squared up.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.77,0:49:40.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,我能坐舒服点\N{\fs90}I'll have a nice ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.44,0:49:42.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的 木筏重新定位中\N{\fs90}Right. Repositioning raft.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.28,0:49:47.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是个靠谱的声音\N{\fs90}That's a reassuring noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.18,0:49:51.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,恩 这个是哪里来的\N{\fs90}Er... Where... Where's that come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.38,0:49:52.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,船长 船长\N{\fs90}James. James.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.72,0:49:54.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,-干嘛 -这里是怎么了\N{\fs90}- What? - What's that doing over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.52,0:49:55.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,什么怎么了\N{\fs90}What's what doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.96,0:49:57.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,所有的竹子都散架了\N{\fs90}All this bamboo's come off.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.59,0:49:59.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,你解开了什么\N{\fs90}What have you untied?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.02,0:50:01.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我解开了在前面的一根绳子\N{\fs90}I've untied the piece of string at the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.55,0:50:05.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是 看 半个竹筏都不见了\N{\fs90}But, look, half the craft is disappearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.21,0:50:09.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为竹筏瓦解的太快了\N{\fs90} As the raft was disintegrating fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.12,0:50:11.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们不得不快点回到岸上\N{\fs90}we had to get it to shore quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.40,0:50:13.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,开动这台机器\N{\fs90}Firing up the machine!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.14,0:50:18.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,悲伤的是 大猩猩在控制速度\N{\fs90}Sadly, though, Jeremy's turn of speed
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.78,0:50:20.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,只会让一切变得更糟\N{\fs90}only made things worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.68,0:50:22.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,马力 马力 来啊\N{\fs90}Power! Power! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.85,0:50:24.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,慢点\N{\fs90}Slow down!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.22,0:50:27.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,它在解体\N{\fs90}It's falling apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.82,0:50:30.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,-看它要沉了 -慢一点\N{\fs90}Look, he's going down! Slow down!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.46,0:50:32.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,慢\N{\fs90}Slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.37,0:50:43.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,你不能放车在上面了 对吧\N{\fs90}You can't put cars on that, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.24,0:50:45.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我们营救了詹姆斯之后\N{\fs90}After we'd rescued James,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.04,0:50:48.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,他愚蠢地建议 这个问题的解决方案\N{\fs90}he stupidly suggested that, to solve the problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.92,0:50:51.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,得要毁了所有人的假日时光\N{\fs90}we should ruin everyone's holiday.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.45,0:51:04.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得这些人应该从这里走开\N{\fs90}I think these people should move out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.39,0:51:07.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的计划是把车拖离沙滩\N{\fs90}My plan was to tow the cars off the beach
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.01,0:51:11.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,拖回码头 我们就能重新开始了\N{\fs90}and back to the harbour so we could start again.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.03,0:51:14.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就意味着我需要亚特兰蒂斯人的帮助\N{\fs90}Which meant I'd need the help of the man from Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.93,0:51:18.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,抓住我的手 来了来了 现在放手\N{\fs90}Hold my hand! There! There! There! Now, let me go.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.14,0:51:20.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的就是我 你要松开\N{\fs90}Yeah, that's me. You have to let...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.44,0:51:22.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦小心我的胳膊 快放开我 我可以的\N{\fs90}Oh, mind my arm! Let me go now. I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.87,0:51:24.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不喜欢这个\N{\fs90}I don't like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.58,0:51:30.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,走开\N{\fs90}Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.09,0:51:41.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈蒙德 把这两个绑起来然后给我个赞\N{\fs90}Hammond, tie both of them to this and give me a thumbs up.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.24,0:51:43.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果詹姆斯把这些一路\N{\fs90}If James gets those onto the road,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.24,0:51:44.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,带到码头的地方\N{\fs90}all the way back up to the harbour,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.98,0:51:48.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,再造一个竹筏 载上车\N{\fs90}build another raft, get them loaded on...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.33,0:51:51.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,把它们带回去 这要花上好几天\N{\fs90}...bring them back, it's gonna take days.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.44,0:51:57.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好了 -不要站在附近\N{\fs90}- OK. - Don't stand near the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.24,0:51:58.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个刹车不管用\N{\fs90}The brakes don't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.41,0:52:03.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,好的\N{\fs90}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.59,0:52:18.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,-又怎么了 -这简直是垃圾\N{\fs90}- Well, now what? - That was rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.70,0:52:23.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后我说 我们该用我那棒呆的船\N{\fs90}I then said we should use my brilliant boat
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.10,0:52:25.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,把这两辆车拖到礁石那\N{\fs90}to tow the cars back to the reef site,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.34,0:52:27.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,这又快又简单\N{\fs90}which would be quicker and easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.01,0:52:35.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,它们在水里了\N{\fs90}They're in the water!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.82,0:52:40.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,哈哈 马力\N{\fs90}Ha-ha! Power!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.12,0:52:41.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,马力 来啊\N{\fs90}Power! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.52,0:52:45.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,耶\N{\fs90}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.12,0:52:47.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,吃我的船吧 船长\N{\fs90}Eat my boat, James May!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.80,0:52:51.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,来啊\N{\fs90}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.93,0:52:57.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,胜利属于船\N{\fs90}Victory is the boat's!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.01,0:53:03.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯那没用的计划\N{\fs90}James May's hopeless plan...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.04,0:53:06.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是啥\N{\fs90}What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.31,0:53:11.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,游泳区里扔了两辆绣标致\N{\fs90}With two rusty Peugeots in his swimming area
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.22,0:53:13.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,沙滩靠椅成了一片废墟\N{\fs90}and his beach furniture in ruins,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.55,0:53:15.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,宾馆的经理已经受够了\N{\fs90}the hotel manager had had enough
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.92,0:53:17.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,给我们下了逐客令\N{\fs90}and ordered us to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.42,0:53:23.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们现在损失了四辆车 一艘船和我们的木筏\N{\fs90}We'd now lost four cars, a boat and our raft.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.56,0:53:27.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,但积极地来看 我们还剩一辆车\N{\fs90}But on the plus side, we still had one car left,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.38,0:53:30.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,和最重要的起重船\N{\fs90}and most importantly, the crane boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.90,0:53:34.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是那天晚上 坏消息来了\N{\fs90}But that night, there was bad news.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.41,0:53:42.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,起重船的船主对我们不是很满意\N{\fs90}The man who owns it is not best pleased with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.35,0:53:45.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,-因为啥 -他把船停租了\N{\fs90}- Because? - He has off-hired it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.28,0:53:48.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,-那么我们就没有起重船了 -没有了\N{\fs90}- We've not got the crane boat? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.19,0:53:51.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是我们手里最有用的东西了 -是啊\N{\fs90}- That was the most useful thing we had. - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.69,0:53:55.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我们能用那辆路虎做些什么\N{\fs90}So what can we possibly do with a Land Rover?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.56,0:53:58.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,-嗯 -嗯 什么\N{\fs90} Well...  Well, what?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.64,0:54:00.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果积极点想\N{\fs90}If I can be positive...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.30,0:54:02.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,路虎的车身大部分都是铝\N{\fs90}The Land Rover's largely aluminium,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.41,0:54:05.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,实际上这用来做珊瑚礁更合适\N{\fs90}which is actually even better for creating a reef.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.20,0:54:06.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,-真的 -但是车在陆地上\N{\fs90}- True. - But it's on the land!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.78,0:54:08.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是个问题 那辆路虎\N{\fs90}Yes, it is true. The Land Rover is--
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.95,0:54:10.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,没用啊 我们别的都没了\N{\fs90}It's irrelevant. We've lost everything else.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.84,0:54:12.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,是 但是如果...\N{\fs90}Yes, but it's good if...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.21,0:54:17.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,我有办法了\N{\fs90}I've had a brainwave.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.02,0:54:18.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 天\N{\fs90}Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.29,0:54:23.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 第二天早上\N{\fs90} And so, the next morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.26,0:54:25.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,巴巴多斯岛上的人们目睹了\N{\fs90}the people of Barbados were treated
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.66,0:54:27.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,一场旷世奇观\N{\fs90}to the magnificent spectacle
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.39,0:54:29.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,一辆路虎靠着内胎\N{\fs90}of a Land Rover gliding majestically
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.86,0:54:31.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,威武滑行\N{\fs90}on a bed of inner tubes
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.46,0:54:34.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,穿越加勒比海\N{\fs90}across the Caribbean Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.23,0:54:36.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在我们在最后一辆车上 这款车很经典\N{\fs90}Here we are on our final car, and it's a classic.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.97,0:54:38.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是一款路虎 Series I\N{\fs90}It's a Series I Land Rover.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.81,0:54:40.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 这是台Series II\N{\fs90}No, it's a Series II.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.37,0:54:42.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是台Series I 大灯是靠在一起的\N{\fs90}It's a Series I. The lights are close together.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.70,0:54:44.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 车门上有辊压\N{\fs90}No, it's got the barrel rolls on the doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.35,0:54:45.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是台Series II\N{\fs90}It's a Series II.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.48,0:54:47.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,-所以还真是Series II -是啊\N{\fs90}- That makes it a Series II? - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.61,0:54:49.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,我记得Series II的大灯是带角度的\N{\fs90}I thought Series IIs had the lights angled.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.07,0:54:50.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得我们进死循环了\N{\fs90}I think we're getting stuck on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.55,0:54:52.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,-这是台路虎 -是一台老路虎\N{\fs90}- It's a Land Rover. - It's an old Land Rover.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.84,0:54:53.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车的好处就在于\N{\fs90}The good thing about it is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.99,0:54:55.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,它被腐蚀的速度远远低于钢制的车\N{\fs90}it corrodes much less quickly than the steel car.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.01,0:54:58.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们还给它贴上了石灰石瓦片\N{\fs90}We've also glued these limestone tiles to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.98,0:55:02.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为多孔的石灰石是让珊瑚成礁\N{\fs90}because porous limestone is the perfect base, foundation,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.50,0:55:04.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,最好的基础\N{\fs90}for coral to start a reef.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.36,0:55:07.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是一台珊瑚礁制造机啊\N{\fs90}This is a coral-reef-making machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.67,0:55:10.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,只不过美中不足的\N{\fs90}In fact, the only fly in the ointment
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.84,0:55:13.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,是它的推进系统\N{\fs90}was its propulsion system.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.67,0:55:16.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我能走得再快点吗 -不能了\N{\fs90}- Can I go a bit faster? - OTHERS: No!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.44,0:55:18.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,你再走快点就进水了\N{\fs90} It's filling with water the faster you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.58,0:55:20.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们就在错误的地方把它弄沉了\N{\fs90}We'll sink it in the wrong place.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.52,0:55:23.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我们最后一辆车 我们最后的机会\N{\fs90}This is our last car, our last chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.45,0:55:26.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们在哭诉 "哦 别走得太快"\N{\fs90}They're bleating on. "Oh, don't go too fast!"
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.62,0:55:29.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,你又跑得太快了 杰里米\N{\fs90} You're going faster again, Jeremy!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.29,0:55:31.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,你在把它往水里拽\N{\fs90}You're pulling it under!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.82,0:55:33.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,放轻松\N{\fs90}Relax!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.39,0:55:35.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我和他到底是不是一个物种\N{\fs90} Am I the same species as that?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.27,0:55:36.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,不\N{\fs90} No.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.24,0:55:38.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰里米 别把它\N{\fs90}Jeremy, don't sink it
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.06,0:55:39.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,在我们到之前就弄沉了\N{\fs90}before we get there!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.90,0:55:42.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,我天 你看见那个了没\N{\fs90}Mother of God! Have you seen that?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.70,0:55:44.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,-啥 -看那边\N{\fs90}- What? - Guys, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.30,0:55:47.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,-哦天 -我去 看那边\N{\fs90} Oh, my God!  Holy cow! Look at it!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.61,0:55:50.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,这可太壮观了\N{\fs90} That is phenomenal!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.64,0:55:52.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,耶 比试下吧\N{\fs90} Yeah! Racing!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.04,0:55:55.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,杰里米 你会弄沉我们的 别跟它比\N{\fs90}Jeremy, you're going to sink us! Don't race it!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.92,0:55:58.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,追上... 噢 我可没时间和那俩耗着\N{\fs90}Catch the... Oh, I haven't got time for these two.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.62,0:56:01.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,好 让我们追上那艘帆船\N{\fs90}Right. Let's go catch that sailing boat!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.76,0:56:05.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢 太棒了\N{\fs90}Oh, brilliant!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.00,0:56:20.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,瞧瞧这个 小太阳\N{\fs90}Watch this, sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.61,0:56:25.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,它是我见过最快的...\N{\fs90}That is the fastest thing I've...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.81,0:56:27.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,为什么它比我还快\N{\fs90}Why is it faster than me?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.15,0:56:39.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们好厉害 微风要战胜马力了\N{\fs90}They're so good, breeze is beating brake horsepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.39,0:56:41.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,我跟不上它\N{\fs90}I cannot keep up with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.36,0:56:48.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们什么时候喝自己的尿\N{\fs90} When do we drink our own urine?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.27,0:56:49.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,看看那玩意\N{\fs90}Look at that thing now!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.14,0:56:59.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,我天\N{\fs90}Bloody Nora!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.15,0:57:09.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,这简直 太棒了\N{\fs90}That is just... fabulous!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.86,0:57:20.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,我本可在这宏伟之作里瞎闹一整天\N{\fs90}I could have buzzed around this amazing machine all day,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.10,0:57:23.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是我还有重要的环保工作要做\N{\fs90}but there was still important environmental work to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.57,0:57:25.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 我很不情愿地离开了\N{\fs90}So, reluctantly, I broke off
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.80,0:57:28.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,重新回到受困的同事身边\N{\fs90}to rejoin my stranded colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.78,0:57:34.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你们还好吗 -并不\N{\fs90}- Are you all right? - Well, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.95,0:57:37.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们刚刚被丢在一辆路虎里随波逐流\N{\fs90}We've just been left to drift in a Land Rover!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.61,0:57:40.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,托你的福 这些瓷砖都没掉\N{\fs90}Fortunately for you, none of these ceramic tiles is loose,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.32,0:57:41.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,要不我就拿它怼你头了\N{\fs90}otherwise I'd chuck it at your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.26,0:57:51.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,你知不知道 实际上它操控起来\N{\fs90}Do you know, I think it actually handles better
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.84,0:57:53.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,比陆地上要好\N{\fs90}than it does on land.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.00,0:57:56.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,不久 我们就要到达礁石区域\N{\fs90}Soon, we will reach the reef site,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.07,0:57:58.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,扎穿内胎 这台路虎就会沉下去\N{\fs90}puncture the inner tubes, the Land Rover will sink,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.07,0:58:01.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,成为一个鳕鱼 黑线鳕 鲤鱼的\N{\fs90}and it will become a safe haven for cod
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.14,0:58:04.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,安全庇护所\N{\fs90}and haddock and...bream.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.58,0:58:09.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,最终 我们到达了指定位置\N{\fs90}Eventually, we reached the site
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.25,0:58:12.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,着手把我们的制礁机凿沉\N{\fs90}and said about scuttling our reef machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.36,0:58:22.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,开火\N{\fs90} Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.53,0:58:25.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,-好样的 -好样的\N{\fs90} Yes!  Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.23,0:58:31.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,走起\N{\fs90} Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.34,0:58:33.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,下去 沉没吧\N{\fs90}Down! Sink!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.37,0:58:34.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,喔\N{\fs90} Whoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.88,0:58:45.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,说实话 所有出色的环保项目\N{\fs90}In truth, all great environmental projects
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.72,0:58:47.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,都是历经过重重困难的\N{\fs90}are beset with problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.92,0:58:51.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,而我们这次 除了詹姆斯以外 都没有出错\N{\fs90}And ours, through no fault of our own, except James's,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.09,0:58:52.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,也是如此\N{\fs90}was no exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.66,0:58:57.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,别弄翻了 停下\N{\fs90}Save it! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.50,0:59:06.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 最后我们的新礁石\N{\fs90}So, in the end, our new reef
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.78,0:59:09.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有像我们想的那样出色\N{\fs90}wasn't quite as spectacular as we'd hoped.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.67,0:59:11.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这只是个开始\N{\fs90}But it was a start,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.14,0:59:13.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,有朝一日它会成为一些\N{\fs90}and one day it'll be the core of something
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.34,0:59:15.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,绵延千里的东西的中心\N{\fs90}a thousand miles long--
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.51,0:59:17.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,在加勒比海中一个崭新又华丽的\N{\fs90}a new and beautiful home
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.38,0:59:20.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,为鳕鱼和黑线鳕而建的新家\N{\fs90}for the cod and the haddock of the Caribbean.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.81,0:59:47.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常感谢\N{\fs90}Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.72,0:59:50.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,由衷地感谢巴巴多斯岛政府\N{\fs90}And a very big thank you to the government of Barbados
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.44,0:59:51.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,对我们拍摄的鼎力相助\N{\fs90}for helping us with that film.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.75,0:59:54.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且我想说在我们建礁石时\N{\fs90}And we'd just like to say no coral was damaged
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.90,0:59:56.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有任何珊瑚受损\N{\fs90}while we were building our reef.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.50,0:59:59.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有 老实说 也没造出来啥珊瑚礁\N{\fs90}No. Or, if we're perfectly honest, created.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.96,1:00:02.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是 我们带着一个绝佳的想法回来了\N{\fs90}However, we came back with a brilliant idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.55,1:00:04.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们看见了 我们很喜欢加勒比\N{\fs90}You see, we liked it in the Caribbean.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.24,1:00:05.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们的工作组也很喜欢加勒比\N{\fs90}Our crews liked it in the Caribbean.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.76,1:00:08.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我想这应该是个好主意 下周\N{\fs90}So we thought it would be a good idea, next week,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.47,1:00:09.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,做一个片子\N{\fs90}to make a film
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.07,1:00:12.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,比较法国 德国 英国之间\N{\fs90}comparing the motoring cultures of the French,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.18,1:00:13.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,汽车文化的差异\N{\fs90}the Dutch and the British Islands.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.72,1:00:15.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,-嗯 是个好主意 -好想法\N{\fs90}- Yeah, it was a great idea. - Brilliant idea.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.55,1:00:17.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是威尔曼先生 我们的制片人\N{\fs90}But Mr Wilman, our producer,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.12,1:00:18.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,他觉得这不是个好主意\N{\fs90}he decided it wasn't a brilliant idea,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.84,1:00:20.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以 取而代之的是\N{\fs90}and that, instead,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.11,1:00:22.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们应该开着三辆旧车去法国北部\N{\fs90}we should go to northern France with three old cars
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.21,1:00:24.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,在雨天里开车兜圈子\N{\fs90}- and drive around in the rain.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.18,1:00:25.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,这确实是我们正在做的\N{\fs90}So that's what we're actually doing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.95,1:00:28.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,随着这个让人失望的消息 是结束的时候了\N{\fs90}And on that terrible disappointment, it's time to end.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.64,1:00:30.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,感谢您的收看\N{\fs90}Thank you so much for watching.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.10,1:00:32.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,感谢您的到来 回见 保重\N{\fs90}Thank you for coming. See you soon. Take care.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.29,1:00:33.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,下次再见\N{\fs90}-  See you next time.
